        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:19PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles north of Many to 9 miles
southwest of Montgomery, or extending from 19 miles west of
Natchitoches to 11 miles southeast of Natchitoches, moving south at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Natchitoches, Many, Provencal, Natchez, Fisher, Robeline,
Hagewood, Flora, Bellwood, Mount Carmel, Kisatchie, Marthaville,
Cypress, Bermuda, Melrose and Gorum.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
